LOCUS       birA                     321 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  birA — E. coli bifunctional biotin-protein ligase / biotin-operon
            repressor (BirA, UniProt P06709), 321 aa; the parent enzyme of the
            AviTag biotinylation system and of the BioID/TurboID
            proximity-labeling ligases..
