                     /synonym="BPL"
                     /note="Bifunctional biotin-[acetyl-CoA-carboxylase] ligase
                     / biotin-operon repressor (BirA), E. coli K12; UniProt
                     P06709, 321 aa, ~35.3 kDa. Three-domain architecture: an
                     N-terminal winged helix-turn-helix DNA-binding domain, a
                     central catalytic domain (seven-stranded mixed beta-sheet
                     bearing the active site and the biotin-binding GRGRRG loop,
                     here at residues 115-120, 1-based), and a C-terminal
                     antiparallel beta-sheet domain. Catalyses biotinylation in
                     two steps: biotin + ATP -> biotinoyl-5'-AMP, then transfer
                     of biotin to a specific lysine of the acceptor substrate.
                     Bio-5'-AMP also acts as corepressor, driving
                     homodimerization and sequence-specific binding to the bioO
                     operator to repress the biotin biosynthesis operon. Parent
                     enzyme of the AviTag/BAP site-specific biotinylation system
                     and of the engineered proximity-labeling ligases BioID
                     (R118G), TurboID and miniTurbo."
